Review:
I kicked and screamed a little through this book with some of the perceptions that were being presented. I struggled with it, I talked with others about it, and most importantly, I opened myself up to it. When I finally came to the end of it, I found myself quite sad and quite frustrated.

Frustrated at my own blind spots and things I have done and sad for how people are treated. I still can't help shake that some of this book is "Stories We Tell Ourselves" about the intentions of others' actions or what people say but it doesn't really matter does it?

What matters is that a problem exists and I now have a better understanding of those problems, so I feel that I can do more to contribute to resolving them and being more compassionate.
